.\" Man page for tk, the Ticket CLI.
.\" View with: man -l man/tk.1
.TH TK 1 "May 2026" "tk 0.0.0" "Ticket Manual"
.SH NAME
tk \- agent-first ticket manager
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B tk
.RI [ global-options ]
.I command
.RI [ arguments ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B tk
is the command-line interface for
.BR Ticket ,
an agent-first tool for managing work items through a simple local
interface and pluggable issue-tracker backends.
.PP
A
.B Ticket
is a backend-agnostic work item with a
.B Ticket Kind
.RB ( task " or " bug )
and a
.B Ticket Status
.RB ( open ", " active ", " blocked ", or " done ).
An
.B Epic
is a backend-agnostic grouping of related
.B Tickets
with its own status
.RB ( open ", " active ", or " done );
an
.B Epic
is not a
.BR Ticket .
.PP
Newly created
.B Tickets
and
.B Epics
are local by default, even when a
.B Primary Backend
is configured.
.B Promotion
is the explicit step that converts a
.B Local Ticket
or
.B Local Epic
into a backend-backed object through the
.BR "Primary Backend" .
.PP
This page is a draft of the
.B tk
CLI surface. Verb names, subcommand layouts, and any flags not stated in
the project README, CONTEXT.md, or ADRs are proposed here for discussion.
Storage layout, sync and conflict handling,
.B Workspace
creation, the
.B Backend Adapter
interface, and the
.B Mutation Type
vocabulary are open design areas and are not pinned down by this page.
.SH COMMANDS
.SS Repository setup
.TP
.B tk init
Initialize the
.B Repository Store
for the current version-control repository. The
.B Repository Store
is shared by all
.B Workspaces
for the repository and is untracked local state by default (ADR 0001).
.SS Creating tickets and epics
.TP
\fBtk add\fR [\fB\-\-epic\fR|\fB\-\-bug\fR] [\fB\-\-parent\fR \fIEPIC\fR]
Create a new
.B Local Ticket
or
.BR "Local Epic" .
Without
.B \-\-bug
or
.BR \-\-epic ,
the new
.B Ticket
has
.B Ticket Kind
.BR task .
.B \-\-bug
and
.B \-\-epic
are mutually exclusive;
.B Epic
is not a
.BR "Ticket Kind" .
.B \-\-parent
adds the new
.B Ticket
to an existing
.B Epic
and is not valid with
.BR \-\-epic .
.IP
.B tk add
opens
.B $EDITOR
on a template if standard input is a terminal, or reads standard input
otherwise. The first non-blank line is the title; lines after the first
blank line form the description. This is the same format as
.BR git\-commit (1).
An empty title cancels the
.BR Mutation .
.IP
On success,
.B tk add
prints the new identifier on standard output.
.SS Listing
.TP
\fBtk list\fR [\fB\-\-all\fR]
List
.B Tickets
and
.BR Epics ,
rendered as a tree in which each
.B Epic
groups its child
.BR Tickets .
.B Tickets
that do not belong to an
.B Epic
and
.B Epics
that have no children appear at the top level. Default views include
both
.B Local Tickets
and
.BR "Backend Tickets" ,
and each row identifies the item's
.BR Origin .
.IP
Each row begins with a status glyph, followed by the identifier, an
.B Origin
tag, a type tag (\fB[epic]\fR for
.BR Epics ,
\fB[bug]\fR for
.B Ticket Kind
.BR bug ;
.B Ticket Kind
.B task
is unmarked), and the title.
.IP
Inside a
.B Workspace
scoped to an
.BR Epic ,
the list narrows to that
.BR Epic 's
.BR Tickets .
With
.BR \-\-all ,
or in a
.B Workspace
without an
.B Epic
.BR "Workspace Scope" ,
the list is repository-wide. A
.B Workspace Scope
on a
.B Ticket
does not narrow the list.
.IP
When the listing is narrowed by an
.B Epic
.BR "Workspace Scope" ,
a banner identifying the active scope is printed to standard error so
it does not appear in piped output. When standard output is a terminal,
a status legend and a summary count are appended on standard output.
.SS Showing
.TP
\fBtk show\fR [\fIID\fR]
Show a single
.B Ticket
or
.BR Epic .
Without
.IR ID ,
shows the
.B Workspace Scope
target.
.SS Updating fields
.TP
\fBtk update\fR [\fIID\fR] \fIflags\fR
Change fields on an existing
.B Ticket
or
.BR Epic .
This is the post-hoc form for field changes; each invocation records one
or more
.BR Mutations .
The exact flag set is part of the open CLI design discussion. Candidates
include
.B Ticket Status
and
.B Epic Status
changes, description edits,
.B Dependency
add and remove, and
.B Epic
membership changes via
.BR \-\-parent .
Without
.IR ID ,
acts on the
.B Workspace Scope
target.
.SS Promotion
.TP
\fBtk promote\fR [\fIID\fR]
Promote a
.B Local Ticket
or
.B Local Epic
to a backend-backed object through the
.BR "Primary Backend" .
.B Promotion
converts the same
.B Ticket
or
.B Epic
in place; it does not create a separate
.B Backend Ticket
alongside the local one.
.SS Workspaces
.TP
.B tk workspace
Print the current
.B Workspace Scope
or report that the
.B Workspace
has none.
.TP
\fBtk workspace set\fR \fIID\fR
Set the
.B Workspace Scope
for the current
.BR Workspace .
.TP
.B tk workspace clear
Remove the
.B Workspace Scope
from the current
.BR Workspace .
.TP
\fBtk workspace new\fR \fIID\fR
Create a new
.B Workspace
scoped to the given
.B Ticket
or
.BR Epic .
Exact creation behavior is an open design area.
.SS Syncing and the Mutation Log
.TP
.B tk sync
Apply pending
.B Mutations
through the
.BR "Primary Backend" 's
.B Backend Adapter
and pull updates for
.B Backend Tickets
and
.B Backend Epics
into the
.BR "Repository Store" .
Conflict handling is an open design area.
.TP
\fBtk log\fR [\fIID\fR] [\fB\-\-pending\fR]
Show the
.BR "Mutation Log" .
With
.IR ID ,
restricts to
.B Mutations
that apply to that
.B Ticket
or
.BR Epic .
With
.BR \-\-pending ,
restricts to
.B Mutations
that have not yet been applied to a backend.
.SS Backends
.TP
.B tk backend list
List configured
.B Backends
and identify the
.BR "Primary Backend" .
.TP
\fBtk backend add\fR \fINAME\fR \fITYPE\fR [\fIadapter-options\fR]
Register a
.B Backend
under a local
.IR NAME .
.I TYPE
selects the
.BR "Backend Adapter" .
.TP
\fBtk backend remove\fR \fINAME\fR
Remove a configured
.BR Backend .
Errors if pending
.B Mutations
target that
.BR Backend .
.TP
\fBtk backend set\-primary\fR \fINAME\fR
Mark the named
.B Backend
as the
.BR "Primary Backend" .
.SH WORKSPACE SCOPE
A
.B Workspace
is a local checkout context, usually a git worktree, that may have a
.B Workspace Scope
referencing exactly one
.B Ticket
or
.BR Epic .
.B Workspace Scope
is local-only and is not synced to backends.
.PP
When a command accepts an optional
.IR ID ,
the
.I ID
defaults to the scoped
.B Ticket
or
.B Epic
if the
.B Workspace
has a
.BR "Workspace Scope" .
Scoped command output identifies the active
.B Workspace Scope
so that humans and agents can tell scoped results from repository-wide
results.
.SH EXAMPLES
Capture a follow-up locally:
.PP
.RS 4
.nf
tk add <<EOF
Investigate flaky login retry

Repro is intermittent on the staging cluster.
First seen 2026-04-30.
EOF
.fi
.RE
.PP
Capture a bug:
.PP
.RS 4
.nf
tk add \-\-bug <<EOF
Fix login timeout on slow networks

Symptom: 504 from /auth after ~30s on connections under 1 Mbps.
EOF
.fi
.RE
.PP
Group related work under a new
.B Local Epic
and add a
.B Ticket
to it:
.PP
.RS 4
.nf
tk add \-\-epic <<EOF
Jira backend

Map Tickets and Epics to Jira issues through a Backend Adapter.
EOF

tk add \-\-parent EP-3 <<EOF
Map Jira issue types to Ticket Kinds

Decide on the bug/task split and how Epic membership maps to Jira links.
EOF
.fi
.RE
.PP
List the
.BR Workspace 's
scoped work, or ignore
.B Workspace Scope
to list everything in the repository:
.PP
.RS 4
.nf
tk list
tk list \-\-all
.fi
.RE
.PP
Promote a curated
.B Local Ticket
to the
.BR "Primary Backend" :
.PP
.RS 4
.nf
tk promote TK-12
.fi
.RE
.PP
Inspect pending local intent before syncing:
.PP
.RS 4
.nf
tk log \-\-pending
tk sync
.fi
.RE
.SH SEE ALSO
The project README, CONTEXT.md (domain glossary), and the ADRs under
.IR docs/adr/ .
.SH BUGS
This is a design-phase project; no implementation exists yet.
